              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The target was in all cases a piece of magnesium",
                "ribbon of 99.97% purity."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "IOCH"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A thick target of magnesium was bombarded in",
                "air for about 10 minutes by an ion beam of 3 MeV",
                "energy and about 0.9 microampere intensity. At the",
                "end of the exposure the target was at once placed at",
                "the window of the electroscope. The measured activity,",
                "as a function of time, was plotted on a logarithmic",
                "scale. The half-life determined from the linear",
                "portion, after due allowance for the natural leak and",
                "background activity of longer life. Several runs were",
                "made to determine the transmutation functions by",
                "using the now standard method of exposing a pile of",
                "thin magnesium foils to the action of the deuteron",
                "beam and then separating the foils and measuring",
                "their activity separately."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The variation in the yield of transmutations as a",
                "function of the energy of the incident particle has",
                "been called the excitation function, or more properly",
                "the voltage transmutation function. The Gamow formula",
                "for the variation in number of transmutation, N, with",
                "voltage, V, is the following: N=k*V**(-1)*exp(-S)",
                "where k is a constant of proportionality and S is",
                "calculated using kinematic parameters and binding",
                "energies."
              ]
            }
          ],
